npc/arif: Before you rush in — look around. This is the last stretch before the core, and it's built as a maze on purpose.
npc/arif: The House shaped it to lose the ones who come hunting it — investigators, reporters, anyone trying to shut the judol machine down. Dead ends, false turns, corridors that fold back on themselves.
npc/arif: The footing lies too. Some platforms look solid and drop the instant you trust them — the same "sure thing" this place always sold. I trusted one once; it held just long enough, then there was nothing under me at all.
npc/arif: Get turned around in here and you can wander until you give up. That's the design — not to kill you, just to lose you.
npc/arif: So keep your bearings, don't trust the shiny footing, and keep moving toward the core. It's an easy place to lose your way in — do you need my help?
